@node INTRO

                        Security System V2.0

 
 First of all, I'm sorry for the poor english in this guide, but after all
this isn't my native language.

 This is the second generation of Security System, it has been totally 
re-writting using SAS-C V6.1.

 Security is ment to protect your System against the intruder's menace, it
will not allow anyone to BOOT from HD without an Username. People can
still boot from floppies but they can't mess in your HARDDISK partitions 
because they will be Write-Protected. Many people is using it to
protect their harddisk against LITLE BROTHERS.

@endnode
@node INST

 To install this program you must call it from your "S:user-startup"
and certify yourself that doesn't appeared any shell-window. this
will disable the ability of CRTL-C breaking.
 To avoid the shell window, you must redirect commands outputs
to the NIL: device.. 
 E.g. 	
	Addbuffers >NIL: DH0: 30


---
 To uninstall just delete the "passwd" call from "S:user-startup".


@endnode

@node LOGIN

 To enter login mode, you must call Passwd from cli without any argument.

 To ensure the safety of your computer you must enter in LOGIN mode
before any CLI-SHELL window appeared. This will disable the ability of
sending the CTRL-C signal to the startup-sequence.

@endnode

@node LOGOUT

 To ensure that your system will be protected against Nasty Intruders
you must run Passwd from the Workbench Icon. This operation will
LOCK all the Harddisk partitions especified in the acct Editor.
 Locked partitions remain Write-Protected even after the computer been
turned off.

  NOTE: If you forget to run the LOGOUT, your system will be
umprotected!!

@endnode

@node ACCT


                           Acct Editor V2.0


 To enter Acct Editor mode, you must run Passwd from cli, and specify the 
argument root.

1>Passwd root

 This will enable the Acct editor. In this editor you can define the
Usernames allowed to enter in your system.
 Accts are defined by an UserName,ID level, and passwd. UserNames are
personalize the Login process, each UserName must have an ID level
that will enable him to Unlock all the drives with an ID level
bellow the User ID. This feature enables the system owner to
enable or disable the Write acess of partition to a certain user.
 Passwords are used to protect the system against ALIENS.

 Uhmm there usage of the editor is quiet simple, just press the buttons
and find out their usage..

 New User    - Creates a new username valid for your system
 Delete User - Erases a user selected from Users-List
 User ID     - Set a new ID level for the selected user
 User Passwd -  "  "  "  Passwd    "   "    "       "

 Funny Button - will search for all your availiable VOLUMES
 New Drive    - Creates a new Drive 
 Delete Drive - Erases a Drive from the Drives List
 Drive Name   - Changes the drive Name
 Drive ID     - Set a new ID level  for the selected Drive

@endnode

